<subSubSection pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="40.[189,310,1262,1288]" box="[189,310,1262,1288]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1262,1288]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1262,1288]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[189,1399,1312,1414]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
The male of 
<taxonomicName authority="Fonseca-Ferreira &amp; Guadanucci &amp; Yamamoto &amp; Brescovit, 2021" authorityName="Fonseca-Ferreira &amp; Guadanucci &amp; Yamamoto &amp; Brescovit" authorityYear="2021" box="[344,540,1312,1338]" class="Arachnida" family="Idiopidae" genus="Idiops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mocambo" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[344,540,1312,1338]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Idiops mocambo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[548,640,1312,1338]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from other Neotropical species by anterior region of the carapace in a pointed shape (
<figureCitation box="[531,640,1350,1376]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="41.[189,232,1856,1882]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,797,1817]" captionTargetId="figure-121@41.[189,1398,797,1817]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="Fig. 23. Idiops mocambo Fonseca-Ferreira, Guadanucci &amp; Brescovit sp. nov., ♂, holotype (MPEG 0110). A. Prosoma (dorsal view). B. Prosoma (ventral view).C. Part of palp (retrolateral view). D–F. Palpal bulb. D. Dorsal view. E. Retrolateral view.F. Prolateral view. G. Tibia, metatarsus and tarsus I (prolateral view). H. Tibial apophysis (prolateral view). I. Tibial apophysis and metatarsus I (dorsal view). Abbreviation: K = keel. Abbreviation: K = keel. Scale bars: A–G, I = 1 mm; H = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761330" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5761330/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 23A</figureCitation>
), sternum with distinct black edges (
<figureCitation box="[1075,1180,1350,1376]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="41.[189,232,1856,1882]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,797,1817]" captionTargetId="figure-121@41.[189,1398,797,1817]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="Fig. 23. Idiops mocambo Fonseca-Ferreira, Guadanucci &amp; Brescovit sp. nov., ♂, holotype (MPEG 0110). A. Prosoma (dorsal view). B. Prosoma (ventral view).C. Part of palp (retrolateral view). D–F. Palpal bulb. D. Dorsal view. E. Retrolateral view.F. Prolateral view. G. Tibia, metatarsus and tarsus I (prolateral view). H. Tibial apophysis (prolateral view). I. Tibial apophysis and metatarsus I (dorsal view). Abbreviation: K = keel. Abbreviation: K = keel. Scale bars: A–G, I = 1 mm; H = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761330" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5761330/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 23B</figureCitation>
) and by the apical branch of the tibial apophysis in rectangular shape (
<figureCitation box="[796,943,1388,1414]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="41.[189,232,1856,1882]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,797,1817]" captionTargetId="figure-121@41.[189,1398,797,1817]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="Fig. 23. Idiops mocambo Fonseca-Ferreira, Guadanucci &amp; Brescovit sp. nov., ♂, holotype (MPEG 0110). A. Prosoma (dorsal view). B. Prosoma (ventral view).C. Part of palp (retrolateral view). D–F. Palpal bulb. D. Dorsal view. E. Retrolateral view.F. Prolateral view. G. Tibia, metatarsus and tarsus I (prolateral view). H. Tibial apophysis (prolateral view). I. Tibial apophysis and metatarsus I (dorsal view). Abbreviation: K = keel. Abbreviation: K = keel. Scale bars: A–G, I = 1 mm; H = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761330" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5761330/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 23G–H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
