</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="41.[189,581,311,372]" box="[234,581,311,337]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,298,311,337]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Male</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[313,418,311,337]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">holotype</typeStatus>
MPEG 0110)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="41.[189,581,311,372]" box="[189,465,346,372]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
HABITUS. See 
<figureCitation box="[353,460,346,372]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="41.[189,232,1856,1882]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,797,1817]" captionTargetId="figure-121@41.[189,1398,797,1817]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="Fig. 23. Idiops mocambo Fonseca-Ferreira, Guadanucci &amp; Brescovit sp. nov., ♂, holotype (MPEG 0110). A. Prosoma (dorsal view). B. Prosoma (ventral view).C. Part of palp (retrolateral view). D–F. Palpal bulb. D. Dorsal view. E. Retrolateral view.F. Prolateral view. G. Tibia, metatarsus and tarsus I (prolateral view). H. Tibial apophysis (prolateral view). I. Tibial apophysis and metatarsus I (dorsal view). Abbreviation: K = keel. Abbreviation: K = keel. Scale bars: A–G, I = 1 mm; H = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761330" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5761330/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 23A</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="41.[189,1060,411,438]" box="[189,1060,411,438]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">MEASUREMENTS. TBL 7.9, CL 3.8, CW 3, LL 0.5, LW 0.7, SL 1.9, SW 1.7.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="41.[189,1399,477,504]" box="[189,1399,477,504]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
COLOR. Brown carapace and legs, except for coxae and trochanters, which are light brown (
<figureCitation box="[1243,1386,477,503]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="41.[189,232,1856,1882]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,797,1817]" captionTargetId="figure-121@41.[189,1398,797,1817]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="Fig. 23. Idiops mocambo Fonseca-Ferreira, Guadanucci &amp; Brescovit sp. nov., ♂, holotype (MPEG 0110). A. Prosoma (dorsal view). B. Prosoma (ventral view).C. Part of palp (retrolateral view). D–F. Palpal bulb. D. Dorsal view. E. Retrolateral view.F. Prolateral view. G. Tibia, metatarsus and tarsus I (prolateral view). H. Tibial apophysis (prolateral view). I. Tibial apophysis and metatarsus I (dorsal view). Abbreviation: K = keel. Abbreviation: K = keel. Scale bars: A–G, I = 1 mm; H = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761330" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5761330/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 23A–B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="41.[187,1400,542,709]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
PROSOMA. Carapace and ocular arrangement as shown in 
<figureCitation box="[880,991,542,569]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="41.[189,232,1856,1882]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,797,1817]" captionTargetId="figure-121@41.[189,1398,797,1817]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="Fig. 23. Idiops mocambo Fonseca-Ferreira, Guadanucci &amp; Brescovit sp. nov., ♂, holotype (MPEG 0110). A. Prosoma (dorsal view). B. Prosoma (ventral view).C. Part of palp (retrolateral view). D–F. Palpal bulb. D. Dorsal view. E. Retrolateral view.F. Prolateral view. G. Tibia, metatarsus and tarsus I (prolateral view). H. Tibial apophysis (prolateral view). I. Tibial apophysis and metatarsus I (dorsal view). Abbreviation: K = keel. Abbreviation: K = keel. Scale bars: A–G, I = 1 mm; H = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761330" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5761330/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 23A</figureCitation>
. Eye tubercle: 0.5 long; 0.9 wide. AME-ALE distance 0.5. Eye diameters: AME 0.2, ALE 0.3, PME 0.2, PLE 0.2. Thoracic fovea procurved (
<figureCitation box="[196,302,613,639]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="41.[189,232,1856,1882]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,797,1817]" captionTargetId="figure-121@41.[189,1398,797,1817]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="Fig. 23. Idiops mocambo Fonseca-Ferreira, Guadanucci &amp; Brescovit sp. nov., ♂, holotype (MPEG 0110). A. Prosoma (dorsal view). B. Prosoma (ventral view).C. Part of palp (retrolateral view). D–F. Palpal bulb. D. Dorsal view. E. Retrolateral view.F. Prolateral view. G. Tibia, metatarsus and tarsus I (prolateral view). H. Tibial apophysis (prolateral view). I. Tibial apophysis and metatarsus I (dorsal view). Abbreviation: K = keel. Abbreviation: K = keel. Scale bars: A–G, I = 1 mm; H = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761330" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5761330/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 23A</figureCitation>
). Labium and sternum without cuspules (
<figureCitation box="[767,872,613,639]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="41.[189,232,1856,1882]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,797,1817]" captionTargetId="figure-121@41.[189,1398,797,1817]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="Fig. 23. Idiops mocambo Fonseca-Ferreira, Guadanucci &amp; Brescovit sp. nov., ♂, holotype (MPEG 0110). A. Prosoma (dorsal view). B. Prosoma (ventral view).C. Part of palp (retrolateral view). D–F. Palpal bulb. D. Dorsal view. E. Retrolateral view.F. Prolateral view. G. Tibia, metatarsus and tarsus I (prolateral view). H. Tibial apophysis (prolateral view). I. Tibial apophysis and metatarsus I (dorsal view). Abbreviation: K = keel. Abbreviation: K = keel. Scale bars: A–G, I = 1 mm; H = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761330" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5761330/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 23B</figureCitation>
). Basal segment of chelicerae with a prolateral row of 5 large teeth and 2 small retrolateral teeth, grouped on basal half, rastellum with 16–18 short and thick spines.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761330" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5761330" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5761330/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" startId="41.[189,232,1856,1882]" targetBox="[189,1398,797,1817]" targetPageId="41">
<paragraph blockId="41.[187,1399,1856,2024]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,279,1856,1882]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 23.</emphasis>
