</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="42.[189,1400,265,328]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
LEGS. Tibia, metatarsus and tarsus I as shown in 
<figureCitation box="[777,887,265,291]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="41.[189,232,1856,1882]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,797,1817]" captionTargetId="figure-121@41.[189,1398,797,1817]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="Fig. 23. Idiops mocambo Fonseca-Ferreira, Guadanucci &amp; Brescovit sp. nov., ♂, holotype (MPEG 0110). A. Prosoma (dorsal view). B. Prosoma (ventral view).C. Part of palp (retrolateral view). D–F. Palpal bulb. D. Dorsal view. E. Retrolateral view.F. Prolateral view. G. Tibia, metatarsus and tarsus I (prolateral view). H. Tibial apophysis (prolateral view). I. Tibial apophysis and metatarsus I (dorsal view). Abbreviation: K = keel. Abbreviation: K = keel. Scale bars: A–G, I = 1 mm; H = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761330" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5761330/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Fig. 23G</figureCitation>
. Leg I with double tibial apophysis, apical branch twice the size of basal branch (
<figureCitation box="[640,775,301,327]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="41.[189,232,1856,1882]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,797,1817]" captionTargetId="figure-121@41.[189,1398,797,1817]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="Fig. 23. Idiops mocambo Fonseca-Ferreira, Guadanucci &amp; Brescovit sp. nov., ♂, holotype (MPEG 0110). A. Prosoma (dorsal view). B. Prosoma (ventral view).C. Part of palp (retrolateral view). D–F. Palpal bulb. D. Dorsal view. E. Retrolateral view.F. Prolateral view. G. Tibia, metatarsus and tarsus I (prolateral view). H. Tibial apophysis (prolateral view). I. Tibial apophysis and metatarsus I (dorsal view). Abbreviation: K = keel. Abbreviation: K = keel. Scale bars: A–G, I = 1 mm; H = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761330" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5761330/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Fig. 23G–I</figureCitation>
). Pseudoscopula: tarsus I–IV totally covered.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[188,1399,367,466]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
PALP. Tibia with spines distributed along margin of retrolateral depression, with large spines at apical and basal ends (
<figureCitation box="[326,434,404,430]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="41.[189,232,1856,1882]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,797,1817]" captionTargetId="figure-121@41.[189,1398,797,1817]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="Fig. 23. Idiops mocambo Fonseca-Ferreira, Guadanucci &amp; Brescovit sp. nov., ♂, holotype (MPEG 0110). A. Prosoma (dorsal view). B. Prosoma (ventral view).C. Part of palp (retrolateral view). D–F. Palpal bulb. D. Dorsal view. E. Retrolateral view.F. Prolateral view. G. Tibia, metatarsus and tarsus I (prolateral view). H. Tibial apophysis (prolateral view). I. Tibial apophysis and metatarsus I (dorsal view). Abbreviation: K = keel. Abbreviation: K = keel. Scale bars: A–G, I = 1 mm; H = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761330" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5761330/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Fig. 23C</figureCitation>
); embolus with lamelliform apical half, keel in retrolateral view and torsion close to sperm duct opening (
<figureCitation box="[467,609,440,466]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="41.[189,232,1856,1882]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,797,1817]" captionTargetId="figure-121@41.[189,1398,797,1817]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="Fig. 23. Idiops mocambo Fonseca-Ferreira, Guadanucci &amp; Brescovit sp. nov., ♂, holotype (MPEG 0110). A. Prosoma (dorsal view). B. Prosoma (ventral view).C. Part of palp (retrolateral view). D–F. Palpal bulb. D. Dorsal view. E. Retrolateral view.F. Prolateral view. G. Tibia, metatarsus and tarsus I (prolateral view). H. Tibial apophysis (prolateral view). I. Tibial apophysis and metatarsus I (dorsal view). Abbreviation: K = keel. Abbreviation: K = keel. Scale bars: A–G, I = 1 mm; H = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761330" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5761330/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Fig. 23D–F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[189,1399,506,569]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">PALP AND LEG MEASUREMENTS. Palp = 7.1 (2.5, 1, 2.6, 1), I = 11.7 (3.4, 1.9, 2.6, 2.6, 1.2), II = 10.3 (2.8, 1.5, 2.3, 2.5, 1.2), III = 9.8 (2.6, 1.4, 1.9, 2.6, 1.3), IV = 12.6 (3.2, 1.8, 3, 3.2, 1.4).</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[189,1399,609,708]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">SPINATION. Palp: Ti r25, Ta 0-0-1. Leg I: Pa v0-0-2, Ti v0-0-2, r1-2-3, Mt p0-0-1, r2-2-2, Ta p1-1-1, r1- 1-1. Leg II: Ti v2-2-3, Mt v3-3-3, r1-1-2, Ta p0-2-0, r1-1-0. Leg III: Ti v0-2-3, Mt v1-2-4, p1-3-4, Ta p0-2-1. Leg IV: Ti v1-1-3, Mt v1-2-4, p1-3-6, Ta p1-1-1.</paragraph>
